Rakuen is a city south of Midgaard, beyond the Eccentric Woodland.
Founded on the Southward Compact as a rejection of Midgaard's ledger culture, governed by shared surplus rather than force.
Haven-Architect Elys Savan designed it around common orchards, cooperative waterworks, and rotating stewardship.
The system worked for a generation before external pressures broke it.
Five eras: founding prosperity, standardization (admired by Kiess), containment (Midgaard used it as a resettlement valve), Ash-and-Iron collapse (poisoned cisterns, dead orchards, forced rationing), and the modern era of refused annexation.
Rakuen petitioned Midgaard for annexation three times; all three were refused on procedural or constitutional grounds.
The city now lacks stable governance and resists integration with five-city institutions.
Cracked Promise Stones mark the boundaries of the original paradise plan.
The Bloom Pavilion's living ivy roof is maintained as proof the founders' vision still partially holds.
Ember Wardens patrol the city. Garden Ledger Clerks guard records that contradict official accounts.
Rakuen persists as proud, exhausted, and ungovernable.
